title: Unraveling the Mystery of Unshakeable Trust: Lessons from an Older Couple’s Unaffected Love (Ep 250)
caption: false

channel_info.title: Robbie Kramer
channel_info.description:
I'm Robbie Kramer 🎙Host of The Inner Confidence Podcast & Founder of Inner Confidence, Inc.

I lived an exhilarating single life filled with adventures and lessons, and ultimately achieved what I had always aspired to – finding an amazing, feminine, and loving wife. 

I believe my experiences provide a rare balance of wild freedom and committed love, equipping me with the insights to help you navigate the complexities of dating and relationships in today's world. Let me guide you to embrace your desires, improve your social prowess, and ultimately attract the partner who aligns with your highest aspirations.

You won’t find any fluffy, new-age, or cringy stuff here, just tested, proven and actionable advice that yields results.

Apply to join our exclusive Inner Confidence Community of ambitious men who are actively working together to achieve their goals faster   ► https://innerconfidence.com/community

You can email me at robbie@innerconfidence.com with any questions or comments.

Their secret is, today's world, you know how many contacts you have? I texted you at two this morning. Your wife could've assumed it was someone else, even if she didn't, and she would've said, who's that texting me? Even though it was on D&D, if it wasn't, she would've woke up, you would've woke up, 2 a.m. in the morning, regardless if it was me or not. And you can't tell me that feels good to anyone, that your partner is getting text messages at two, three in the morning. So, those old people's secret is that they never had to have that emotion. They never had to ask those questions. That wasn't part of their bullshit. You go through my DMs right now, men and women sending me raunchy stuff, negative stuff, positive stuff, but at the end of the day, they never had to go through that. They never had to have that emotion of somebody is trying to get with my partner because if you didn't work or live around that area, go to a grocery store, you didn't see anyone else.
